Designing Crates for Seasonal Storage
When planning your seasonal storage crate design, consider these key factors:

Accurate Measurements for Space Efficiency
Measure the items you plan to store — including bulky or irregular pieces — and design crates that optimize available storage space without wasted gaps. (cratesoflasvegas.com)

Stackable & Space‑Saving Designs
Custom crates can be designed to stack securely, helping you make the most of garage, attic, closet, or business storage space without compromising accessibility. (cratesoflasvegas.com)

Interior Protection Options
Add foam inserts, padding, or divider systems to help keep fragile seasonal items safe from impact and abrasion during storage. (cratesoflasvegas.com)

Labeling & Organization
Clear labeling systems — including printed tags or color‑coded markers — make it easier to identify what’s inside each crate, saving time when packing or unpacking seasonal items. (cratesoflasvegas.com)

